The Centers for Medicare &amp; Medicaid Services (CMS) a federal agency, recently named Baylor Scott &amp; White Medical Center-White Rock, in Dallas, as one of the worst performing hospitals in America.&nbsp;
The dubious 1-star ranking is based on 46 hospital quality measures that CMS uses to compare hospitals nationwide.
Only 248 hospitals nationwide received Medicare&#39;s 1-star designation. This Dallas hospital was one of only seven hospitals in Texas to be named to Medicare&#39;s 1-star list.

&ldquo;When I use a word,&rdquo; Humpty Dumpty said in rather a scornful tone, &ldquo;it means just what I choose it to mean &mdash; neither more nor less.&rdquo;
&ldquo;The question is,&rdquo; said Alice, &ldquo;whether you can make words mean so many different things.&rdquo;
&ldquo;The question is,&rdquo; said Humpty Dumpty, &ldquo;which is to be master &mdash; that&rsquo;s all.&rdquo;
I often think about this quote from Lewis Carroll&rsquo;s book Through the Looking Glass. I find that it fits well to Texas medical malpractice litigation.
